# Agent task → version bump (mandatory)

## Policy

**Any agent** (interactive session, subagent, orchestrator step, or **committer**) that **edits this repository** and **ends with commit and/or `git push`** to the integration branch must **raise the app semver** in the **same change series** so the **admin sidebar** and **storefront footer** stay truthful (`APP_VERSION` / `__APP_VERSION__` come from root **`package.json`** — see **`app-version-cadence.mdc`**).

1. After **each completed task** that produced **tracked file changes** (code, locale JSON, `CHANGELOG.md`, new/changed **`.mdc`**, etc.), run **`npm version patch --no-git-tag-version`** at the repo root (updates **`package.json`** and **`package-lock.json`**).
2. Include that bump **before** **`git push`**, ideally in the **last** commit of the task or the dedicated committer step.
3. When the task touched **`resources/js/`** or Vite, run **`npm run build`** so embedded version strings match.

**Clarification:** “Each prompt” means **each finished agent run that changes the tree**, not a no-op chat turn. If no files are modified, no bump.

**End of user prompt / session:** When the user signals work is **done** (or the agent finishes a substantive request) and **tracked files changed**, bump patch and add **`CHANGELOG.md`** **`[Unreleased]`** bullets **in that same session** — **do not wait** for the word **commit** unless the user explicitly defers versioning. Stale **`footer.version`** / **`APP_VERSION`** confuse operators.

## What this overrides

Loose “docs-only may skip” habits do **not** apply to **agent-delivered** work: if you **commit** a change, **bump patch** unless the only event is a **git revert** that fully restores a previous release (team discretion).

## Changelog

If you add bullet(s) under **`CHANGELOG.md`** `[Unreleased]`, the new **`package.json`** version must stay in sync with release practice — see **`commit-changelog-version.mdc`**.
